  "prompt": "Re the Sochi Olympics online video coverage, if I want to watch an event on streaming video but I cannot watch it live, is there some kind of archive after the event first airs?",
  "response": "Yes, for the Sochi Olympics and similar events, broadcasters typically offer archived streaming video coverage after the event has aired live. This means that you can often find replays of the events on the official Olympic websites or the platforms of broadcasters that held the streaming rights. These archives allow you to watch events on demand, even if you missed the live broadcast. Availability can vary by region and broadcaster, so it's a good idea to check the specific service you plan to use.",
